.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-9::.
4 different games are played: monopoly, snooker, bridge, scrabble
The people use 4 different means of transport: boat, bus, taxi, trike
1. the person playing monopoly is between the person playing scrabble and the person driving the boat##2
2. the person driving the trike is on the far left##1
3. the person driving the trike is on the left or right of the person playing monopoly##3
4. the person playing snooker is somewhere to the right of the person driving the boat##5
5. the person driving the bus is the person driving the bus##1
6. the person playing bridge is not the person driving the taxi##6
7. the person playing scrabble is not to the right of the person playing bridge##8
8. the person driving the boat is not to the left of the person driving the bus##8

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1   |     2     |   3   |    4    |
| Game   | scrabble   | monopoly | bridge | snooker |
| Transport     | trike | bus       | boat  | taxi    |

